Field Detail

ID

public static final java.lang.String ID
Unique identifier for this channel. May be known as "client id", or "channel id", "subscriber id", or "recipient id". This is a unique String that can universally identify the client Id, and should not be confused with {#tv.ux1.entity.Entity.id}, which is the unique id within the datastore.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

SUBSCRIBER_IDS

public static final java.lang.String SUBSCRIBER_IDS
A list of clientId's that are subscribed to this channel. Any message sent to this channel will be distributed to each of these subscribers.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

TOKEN

public static final java.lang.String TOKEN
The token returned from the AppEngine channel service. This is how the server knows what channel to connect you to. This is NOT the same as the clientId, which is our unique identifier for a channel. The token is only relevant to the methods within the GAE framework.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

TV_CODE

public static final java.lang.String TV_CODE
A one- to four-digit numeric code used to subscribe to a TV's channel.

public boolean addSubscriberId(java.lang.String subscriberId)
Convenience method for adding a Subscriber Id to the Set of subscribers on this channel. This method calls the add() method on the underlying Set member.
